The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Guidelines for Eden

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Police have released a list of items that spectators to Thursdays India-Sri Lanka ODI at Eden Gardens will not be allowed to carry.

 Firearms (even licensed ones), transistors or any other battery-operated items, bugles, conch shells, whistles, crackers, cameras, binoculars, mirrors and other glass items, handbags, drinking water in glass or plastic containers are on the not-to-carry list.

 Spectators have been requested to follow the map on the reverse side of the ticket while entering the stadium. They should reach the stadium at least an hour in advance. 

 The traffic department has assured the people of instant help in case of taxi refusal.




